

Q.4
a. What are the benefits of using an abstract method?
b. Explain with an appropriate code example.


Ans:-  

	A.
 	Benefits of abstract Method:-
	Abstract in java avoids code duplication.
	It can enables the code reusability.
	Abstract method in java is highly beneficial in writing shorter codes.
	
	
	A method declared using the abstract keyword within an abstract class and does not have a definition is called an abstract method.
	
	B.
	Example:- 
	
	abstract class Multiply{
	
	
	public abstract int MultiplyTwo (int n1, int n2);
	public abstract int multiplyThree (int n1, int n2, int n3);
	
	public void show() {
	
	System.out.println("Method of abstract class Multiply");
	
	}
	}
	
	Class AbstractMethodEx1 extends Multiply {
	
	public int Multiply Two (int num1, int num2) {
	return num1 * num2;
	}
	
	public int multiplyThree (int num1,num2,int3){
	return num1*num2*num3;
	}
	
	Public static void main (String[] args){
	Multiply Obj = new AbstractMethodEx1();
	System.out.println("Multiplication of 2 numbers: "+ obj.MultiplyTwo(10,50);
	System.out.println("Multiplication of 3 numbers: "+ obj.MultiplyThree(5,8,10));
	
	obj.show();
	}
	}